item.title: Host name..?
item.dc:creator: @ThAt0n36Uy Elijah
item.description:
@ThAt0n36Uy wrote:

No there isn’t. Most people change their IP address and do not know it. They have what you would call a Dynamic IP address. But there are also these things called Proxies, and they allow you to connect through a gateway of sorts. It’s basically like connecting to another computer, which that computer connects to the internet. There are programs you can download that connect you to 1-1million different proxies, that constantly switches between them so you aren’t traced.
